# MOOJ Rules

## Development

1. Start with Central Documentation: Read development/guide.md first
2. Implementation Process: Follow implementation-plan.md steps sequentially
3. Cross-Reference Documentation: Reference guide.md for standards, technical-specification.md for specs
4. Evaluation System: See evaluation-pipeline.md for complete details on the evaluation flow

## Documentation

### Structure
- development/guide.md: Workflow, standards, and progress tracking
- implementation-plan.md: Implementation steps only
- technical-specification.md: Technical specifications and design
- evaluation-pipeline.md: Evaluation flow and implementation details
- deployment-guide.md: Deployment instructions

### Locations
- /docs/: Main documentation
- /backend/docs/: Backend documentation
- /frontend/docs/: Frontend documentation

### Updates
1. When adding features: Mark implementation-plan.md steps done, update guide.md Progress
2. When editing docs: Maintain cross-references, use relative links, update anchors

### Standards
- Use tables of contents and numbered sections
- Place important information first
- Be concise, clear, and consistent
- Review and update documentation alongside code
- Remove outdated information 